1
00:00:11,700 --> 00:00:13,600
She can't go anywhere.

2
00:00:13,667 --> 00:00:16,467
No one can take Mookie from me.

3
00:00:16,533 --> 00:00:20,200
It seems so painful for me
to leave her.

4
00:00:20,267 --> 00:00:22,967
Someone seems to whisper
that I should take care of her.

5
00:00:23,033 --> 00:00:25,333
Your fever will return

6
00:00:25,400 --> 00:00:28,633
if there's still an infection
in your body.

7
00:00:28,700 --> 00:00:32,033
Ma'am Olive said
her leg must be amputated.

8
00:00:32,100 --> 00:00:36,200
Please help me convince mommy
not to amputate my leg.

9
00:00:36,300 --> 00:00:37,100
Please...

10
00:00:37,167 --> 00:00:39,067
I can't bear it if you die!

11
00:00:39,133 --> 00:00:41,367
So I will have
your leg amputated

12
00:00:41,433 --> 00:00:43,533
so that you will
stay with me forever!

13
00:00:43,600 --> 00:00:45,167
Maybe you can help her.

14
00:00:45,233 --> 00:00:46,600
- Wait! I'll go ahead!
- Go, Ma'am.

15
00:00:46,667 --> 00:00:47,600
- I'll leave now.
- Okay, Ma'am.

16
00:00:48,833 --> 00:00:49,600
Doc, Doc.

17
00:00:49,667 --> 00:00:51,100
Let's not do it.

18
00:00:51,167 --> 00:00:52,800
I can't do this to my daughter.

19
00:00:52,867 --> 00:00:54,167
- What's going on?
- The police are here.

20
00:00:54,233 --> 00:00:55,833
Someone reported me again.

21
00:00:55,900 --> 00:00:56,600
Mookie!

22
00:01:30,067 --> 00:01:30,767
Sir, you can't get in.
- Let us in!
- Sir!

23
00:01:31,833 --> 00:01:33,400
- Sir, hold on!
- Get out of the way!

24
00:01:33,467 --> 00:01:35,233
Sir, what's this all about?

25
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:38,200
Someone reported
your illegal practices.

26
00:01:46,500 --> 00:01:50,667
Sir, I've stopped being a doctor
for a long time.

27
00:01:50,733 --> 00:01:54,167
And those who are reporting me
are my business rivals.

28
00:01:54,233 --> 00:01:56,733
In fact,
I am the top distributor

29
00:01:56,800 --> 00:02:01,667
of Vart Liv vitamins
and food supplements in NCR.

30
00:02:01,733 --> 00:02:03,567
That's why a lot
are envious of me.

31
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:08,667
They want to bring me down.

32
00:02:10,733 --> 00:02:11,600
Come on. Move!

33
00:02:31,367 --> 00:02:33,300
Let's go, Ma'am.
I'll help you out.

34
00:02:33,367 --> 00:02:34,567
- Come on.
- Let's go.

35
00:02:34,633 --> 00:02:35,233
Come on, let's go.

36
00:02:36,967 --> 00:02:38,500
Let's go out.
You better stay outside.

37
00:02:38,567 --> 00:02:39,533
Come on, come on, come on.

38
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:45,367
Hurry up.

39
00:02:46,933 --> 00:02:47,500
Come on.

40
00:02:49,733 --> 00:02:50,767
Let's go.

41
00:02:50,833 --> 00:02:52,967
Ma'am, we parked your car
in front of the village.

42
00:02:53,033 --> 00:02:53,600
Okay.

43
00:02:56,033 --> 00:02:57,600
Go on. I'll be fine here.

44
00:02:57,667 --> 00:02:58,467
Thank you.

45
00:03:10,833 --> 00:03:13,233
Oh my God, Mookie!
I'm glad you're okay.

46
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:14,167
You?

47
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:16,400
You did this?

48
00:03:18,967 --> 00:03:22,400
Did you report Dr. Miranda
to the police?

49
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:24,067
No.

50
00:03:24,133 --> 00:03:27,667
I didn't do that because
you'll get in trouble if I do.

51
00:03:27,733 --> 00:03:29,300
But if that was an option,

52
00:03:29,367 --> 00:03:33,233
I'd do it just to stop
your plan with Mookie.

53
00:03:33,300 --> 00:03:37,767
Luckily, someone else reported
that shady Dr. Miranda.

54
00:03:37,833 --> 00:03:40,867
I was just trying to teach
Mookie a lesson.

55
00:03:40,933 --> 00:03:42,133
By what?

56
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:44,633
Bringing her to a doctor
with a revoked license,

57
00:03:44,700 --> 00:03:46,833
and who's willing
to cut her leg off?

58
00:03:46,900 --> 00:03:49,233
I won't have her legs amputated!

59
00:03:49,300 --> 00:03:51,267
Really, Olive?

60
00:03:51,333 --> 00:03:54,533
Or was it only interrupted
because the police came?

61
00:03:54,633 --> 00:03:56,433
You know what, Astrid?

62
00:03:56,500 --> 00:03:57,567
You're already getting
on my nerves

63
00:03:57,633 --> 00:03:59,800
for meddling with my life.

64
00:03:59,867 --> 00:04:00,933
I know what I'm doing.

65
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,167
Wait!

66
00:04:02,233 --> 00:04:04,067
Will you shut up?

67
00:04:04,133 --> 00:04:07,400
Do your job at Artemis Pharmacy.

68
00:04:07,467 --> 00:04:08,900
And I will send you
to Ricamonte Lab in Cebu

69
00:04:08,967 --> 00:04:11,033
first thing in the morning.

70
00:04:11,100 --> 00:04:12,567
Take care of that instead!

71
00:04:12,633 --> 00:04:13,500
Olive, wait.

72
00:04:13,567 --> 00:04:15,833
Just do as I say, Astrid.

73
00:04:15,900 --> 00:04:19,433
Or else, say goodbye
to your position in the company.

74
00:04:33,133 --> 00:04:35,400
Are you still worrying about
your employer's daughter?

75
00:04:40,633 --> 00:04:43,667
I want to know if Mookie's leg
got amputated.

76
00:04:45,067 --> 00:04:47,033
I hope not.

77
00:04:47,100 --> 00:04:48,733
Emma, I hope you don't
take this the wrong way,

78
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:51,767
but I don't think getting
involved in their lives

79
00:04:51,833 --> 00:04:54,033
is part of your job.

80
00:04:54,100 --> 00:04:56,667
We have our own lives.

81
00:04:56,733 --> 00:04:58,033
Well, if you like...

82
00:04:59,533 --> 00:05:00,700
we can adopt a kid.

83
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:08,300
So you don't have to spend time
with a kid unrelated to you.

84
00:05:08,367 --> 00:05:09,167
As for me...

85
00:05:11,033 --> 00:05:12,967
I miss being a father.

86
00:05:14,500 --> 00:05:16,267
And I also want us
to be a family.

87
00:05:18,667 --> 00:05:19,333
Emma?

88
00:05:20,367 --> 00:05:23,100
Are you listening to me?
I'm saying something.

89
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:26,000
You're saying something?

90
00:05:29,100 --> 00:05:32,400
Nothing.
I said let's go to sleep.

91
00:05:40,533 --> 00:05:41,367
My legs!

92
00:05:45,500 --> 00:05:49,667
You're lucky I decided to cancel
your leg amputation for now.

93
00:05:49,733 --> 00:05:51,133
Mommy, thank you.

94
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:52,500
Thank you.

95
00:05:52,567 --> 00:05:54,000
Thank you, Mommy.

96
00:05:57,133 --> 00:06:00,400
But, Mommy,
would you still lock me up here?

97
00:06:02,333 --> 00:06:03,100
Mommy?

98
00:06:04,133 --> 00:06:05,800
Mommy!

99
00:06:05,867 --> 00:06:09,267
Mommy, please! Mommy, please!

100
00:06:09,367 --> 00:06:10,333
Mommy, please!

101
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:12,200
Mommy! Mommy!

102
00:06:13,233 --> 00:06:14,000
Mommy!

103
00:06:15,100 --> 00:06:16,367
Mommy!

104
00:07:08,933 --> 00:07:10,300
Oh my gosh.

105
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:23,300
I can walk again.

106
00:07:24,933 --> 00:07:26,700
I can walk again.

107
00:08:14,367 --> 00:08:16,267
What do you want to say?

108
00:08:18,900 --> 00:08:21,167
Mookie's leg wasn't amputated.

109
00:08:21,267 --> 00:08:23,467
Thank you, Lord.

110
00:08:23,533 --> 00:08:25,767
Come on! You're wasting my time.
I still have to go somewhere.

111
00:08:25,833 --> 00:08:27,700
What are you going to say?

112
00:08:27,767 --> 00:08:30,733
And why aren't you wearing
your leg brace?

113
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:32,200
This, Mommy.

114
00:08:34,633 --> 00:08:35,767
What are you doing?

115
00:08:40,567 --> 00:08:41,467
Mookie?

116
00:08:42,733 --> 00:08:43,767
Look, Mommy.

117
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:49,967
What are you doing? Why are you
forcing yourself to get up?

118
00:08:50,033 --> 00:08:52,433
See, Mommy? I can now stand.

119
00:08:52,500 --> 00:08:54,600
Maybe I can walk again soon.

120
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:00,300
Don't force yourself
to stand up!

121
00:09:00,367 --> 00:09:01,600
Sit down!

122
00:09:01,667 --> 00:09:04,133
Don't ever try to get up again!

123
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:07,300
Your bones can break!
Did you know that?

124
00:09:07,367 --> 00:09:09,133
Don't do that again!

125
00:09:28,133 --> 00:09:28,867
Mommy Emma?
Mookie.

126
00:09:31,933 --> 00:09:35,633
Mommy Emma,
what are you doing here?

127
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:38,033
You don't have work today,
do you?

128
00:09:40,267 --> 00:09:42,667
I wanted to see you.

129
00:09:42,733 --> 00:09:44,200
I'm happy.

130
00:09:44,267 --> 00:09:47,733
I'm glad that
your leg is intact.

131
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:50,233
I saw you standing up.

132
00:10:06,733 --> 00:10:09,633
Mookie should never walk again.
She'll escape.

133
00:10:09,700 --> 00:10:12,667
She's going to leave me.
She should never walk again.

134
00:10:12,733 --> 00:10:13,933
I won't let that happen.

135
00:10:26,700 --> 00:10:27,367
No.

136
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:29,967
No.

137
00:10:30,033 --> 00:10:31,900
No! No!

138
00:10:31,967 --> 00:10:33,467
No!

139
00:10:44,400 --> 00:10:47,533
Mookie, please smile.

140
00:10:49,333 --> 00:10:54,400
How can you smile
if you're extremely sad?

141
00:10:57,367 --> 00:11:01,433
You know,
being happy is a choice.

142
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:04,467
If you choose to be happy...

143
00:11:06,100 --> 00:11:09,533
no matter what sadness
comes into your life,

144
00:11:09,633 --> 00:11:11,300
it will not affect you.

145
00:11:11,367 --> 00:11:19,500
Mommy Emma,
can you teach me to smile?

146
00:11:19,567 --> 00:11:20,400
Okay.

147
00:11:23,633 --> 00:11:25,233
Close your eyes.

148
00:11:32,767 --> 00:11:36,400
Think about the happiest event
in your life.

149
00:11:37,767 --> 00:11:40,267
Focus on that.

150
00:11:40,333 --> 00:11:42,900
Don't let any other thoughts
come in.

151
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:45,667
Think of happy things.

152
00:11:48,233 --> 00:11:52,067
Mom,
I thought you would never come.

153
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:56,667
I thought I'd never
see you again.

154
00:11:56,733 --> 00:12:00,367
There's nothing a mother
wouldn't do for her child.

155
00:12:01,400 --> 00:12:03,633
I don't want to lose you.

156
00:12:03,700 --> 00:12:05,567
So I'll never leave you.

157
00:12:28,033 --> 00:12:30,700
Open your eyes, Dear.

158
00:12:34,267 --> 00:12:35,067
There.

159
00:12:36,133 --> 00:12:37,433
You're smiling.

160
00:12:39,633 --> 00:12:42,533
Do that whenever you're sad.

161
00:12:45,400 --> 00:12:47,167
What are you thinking?

162
00:12:47,233 --> 00:12:48,900
Why do you seem so happy?

163
00:12:51,400 --> 00:12:54,433
The moment you read me
a storybook.

164
00:12:58,800 --> 00:13:05,933
Mommy Emma, can you continue
reading the storybook for me?

165
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:10,000
Of course.

166
00:13:13,100 --> 00:13:14,733
Where's your book?

167
00:13:14,800 --> 00:13:15,767
Over there.

168
00:13:19,867 --> 00:13:23,700
I will never let you
walk again, Mookie.

169
00:13:23,800 --> 00:13:26,667
You're mine forever.

170
00:13:26,733 --> 00:13:28,333
You're mine.

171
00:13:33,933 --> 00:13:34,767
Hello?

172
00:13:35,667 --> 00:13:37,900
Jireh Vet-Aid Pharmacy?

173
00:13:37,967 --> 00:13:41,567
I'm on my way to pick up
all the Canixidol I ordered.

174
00:13:42,933 --> 00:13:45,467
I'll get
all the stocks available.

175
00:13:51,500 --> 00:13:57,067
One night, Lily and Rosie
were gathering wood together.

176
00:14:06,167 --> 00:14:09,400
Rosie, we've already got a lot.
So we're going home now.

177
00:14:09,467 --> 00:14:10,800
Yes, Mom.

178
00:14:10,867 --> 00:14:14,633
They're on their way home when
suddenly, someone grabs Rosie.

179
00:14:14,700 --> 00:14:16,867
It's the scary witch, Iris.

180
00:14:16,933 --> 00:14:18,267
Come here.

181
00:14:18,333 --> 00:14:20,000
- You're mine from now on.
- Mom! Mom!

182
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:21,433
- Let go of my daughter!
- Mom!

183
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:25,267
There's a villain
in the version of your book?

184
00:14:25,333 --> 00:14:25,967
Yes.

185
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:30,667
The author added it
to make it more exciting.

186
00:14:30,767 --> 00:14:31,767
Oh.

187
00:14:32,900 --> 00:14:35,267
Iris took Rosie.

188
00:14:35,867 --> 00:14:36,467
- Mom!
- No!

189
00:14:36,533 --> 00:14:37,767
Dear!

190
00:14:37,833 --> 00:14:42,367
Your daughter is mine now!
I will never return her to you!

191
00:14:42,433 --> 00:14:44,900
See, Mommy? I can stand up now.

192
00:14:44,967 --> 00:14:47,200
Maybe I can walk again soon.

193
00:14:56,533 --> 00:14:57,300
What's that?

194
00:15:02,800 --> 00:15:03,767
Damn it!

195
00:15:14,533 --> 00:15:16,300
Damn it!

196
00:15:16,367 --> 00:15:18,567
Why did it have to happen today?

197
00:15:18,633 --> 00:15:21,633
Lily is catching up
with Iris and Rosie.

198
00:15:21,700 --> 00:15:22,767
- What are you doing?
- She's my daughter!

199
00:15:22,833 --> 00:15:24,533
So I will fight for her
no matter what!

200
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:25,867
Your daughter is already mine!

201
00:15:25,933 --> 00:15:27,000
No!

202
00:15:27,067 --> 00:15:30,300
But Lily won't let Iris
take Rosie away.

203
00:15:30,367 --> 00:15:31,800
Dear, faster!

204
00:15:31,867 --> 00:15:32,667
Faster!

205
00:15:35,300 --> 00:15:37,167
No! Your daughter is mine!

206
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:40,100
- Mom!
- Dear!

207
00:15:40,167 --> 00:15:42,133
- Rosie is mine!
- Let go of her!

208
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:43,367
Your daughter is mine!

209
00:16:13,033 --> 00:16:13,700
Give me your cellphone!

210
00:16:13,767 --> 00:16:15,733
Let go of me! Stop it!

211
00:16:15,800 --> 00:16:17,300
Let go of me!

212
00:16:19,167 --> 00:16:20,467
People are coming!

213
00:16:20,533 --> 00:16:21,133
Hurry up!
Let's go!

214
00:16:31,967 --> 00:16:36,633
From then on, Iris has never
shown up to Lily and Rosie.

215
00:16:39,733 --> 00:16:41,100
Mommy Emma...

216
00:16:42,200 --> 00:16:44,433
Iris is pitiful, too.

217
00:16:44,500 --> 00:16:46,100
You feel sorry for the villain?

218
00:16:47,567 --> 00:16:52,833
She only became bad
because she had no family.

219
00:16:52,900 --> 00:16:54,600
She has no daughter.

220
00:16:54,667 --> 00:16:57,133
That's why she wanted
to take Rosie.

221
00:17:00,100 --> 00:17:02,867
You're a very kind kid, Mookie.

222
00:17:02,933 --> 00:17:06,300
You want to understand
even the villain.

223
00:17:07,300 --> 00:17:10,933
That's the truth, Mommy Emma.

224
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:15,433
Lily and Rosie
have a happy ending.

225
00:17:15,533 --> 00:17:17,067
Iris has none.

226
00:17:23,300 --> 00:17:24,400
Hold on.

227
00:17:24,467 --> 00:17:28,367
Why do we have to go
this far for a card game?

228
00:17:29,700 --> 00:17:31,567
- Stop laughing. Answer me.
- Go ahead.

229
00:17:31,633 --> 00:17:33,767
Keep on complaining!

230
00:17:33,833 --> 00:17:35,367
You will go home happy.

231
00:17:35,433 --> 00:17:36,933
They're not good at playing.

232
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:39,600
But they bet a lot.

233
00:17:39,667 --> 00:17:41,433
Come on.
So, we can earn some money.

234
00:17:41,500 --> 00:17:42,367
Look at you now. Let's go.
Hey.

235
00:17:44,133 --> 00:17:45,433
I think there's an accident.

236
00:17:45,500 --> 00:17:46,467
- Oh, yes.
- Come on.

237
00:17:46,533 --> 00:17:47,933
- Let's see what's going on.
- Okay, okay.

238
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:48,567
Hey!

239
00:17:48,667 --> 00:17:50,367
What's going on there?

240
00:17:50,433 --> 00:17:51,267
Oh, wait.
Hey.

241
00:17:53,300 --> 00:17:54,333
Give way.

242
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:55,833
- Move, move move.
- Wait. Don't touch her yet.

243
00:17:55,900 --> 00:17:57,667
Where's the ambulance?
Did someone call already?

244
00:17:57,733 --> 00:17:59,533
- Yes, someone called.
- Kutsy, it's Madam Beautiful!

245
00:17:59,600 --> 00:18:00,800
It's her!

246
00:18:00,867 --> 00:18:03,600
Did you call an ambulance?
Does it mean she's still okay?

247
00:18:03,667 --> 00:18:04,600
Check on her.

248
00:18:04,667 --> 00:18:06,133
- Check her phone.
- Madam?

249
00:18:06,200 --> 00:18:07,533
Yes, she's still okay.

250
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:08,833
She's still alive.

251
00:18:08,900 --> 00:18:10,400
- There's still a pulse.
- Where is the ambulance?

252
00:18:10,467 --> 00:18:11,933
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

253
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:14,000
I know what you're doing.

254
00:18:14,067 --> 00:18:15,767
Are you going to steal it?

255
00:18:15,833 --> 00:18:17,700
Watch your mouth.

256
00:18:17,767 --> 00:18:19,933
I'm not what you think I am.

257
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:21,600
She's my daughter's employer.

258
00:18:21,700 --> 00:18:24,100
Her name is Olive Caparas.

259
00:18:24,167 --> 00:18:25,400
You can check her ID.

260
00:18:25,467 --> 00:18:28,267
You'll see
an Artemis Pharmacy's ID.

261
00:18:28,333 --> 00:18:30,300
Because she owns that.

262
00:18:30,367 --> 00:18:31,833
How dare you accuse me.

263
00:18:31,900 --> 00:18:33,000
Check her ID.

264
00:18:33,067 --> 00:18:34,367
Go ahead. Prove it.

265
00:18:34,433 --> 00:18:35,267
Where's her bag?

266
00:18:35,333 --> 00:18:36,400
She doesn't have
any things on her.

267
00:18:36,467 --> 00:18:38,867
Wait, wait. She has a car.
Maybe it's in her car.

268
00:18:38,933 --> 00:18:39,600
- I'll go and check.
- Check it out.
Wait.

269
00:18:43,700 --> 00:18:45,767
Your wound is almost healed.

270
00:18:50,667 --> 00:18:51,500
Can you get up?

271
00:18:52,100 --> 00:18:53,233
Yes.

272
00:18:53,300 --> 00:18:54,267
Hold on to me.

273
00:18:57,333 --> 00:18:59,600
Thank you, Mommy Emma.

274
00:18:59,667 --> 00:19:01,967
Do you want
to practice walking?

275
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:05,000
I don't want to.

276
00:19:05,067 --> 00:19:11,967
My mom told me
not to try to walk anymore.

277
00:19:12,033 --> 00:19:14,567
Why? Is that what
your doctor told you?

278
00:19:15,700 --> 00:19:18,133
My mom is my only doctor.

279
00:19:22,067 --> 00:19:26,033
Didn't you seek a second opinion
from another doctor?

280
00:19:26,100 --> 00:19:27,300
No, I didn't.

281
00:19:35,067 --> 00:19:36,233
How about you?

282
00:19:36,300 --> 00:19:38,667
Do you want to practice walking?

283
00:19:42,967 --> 00:19:44,600
Of course, I do.

284
00:19:44,667 --> 00:19:48,467
I want to walk because
I don't want to lose my leg.

285
00:19:48,533 --> 00:19:50,167
But...

286
00:19:50,233 --> 00:19:52,300
I can help you.

287
00:19:52,367 --> 00:19:54,767
Do you want to try it?

288
00:19:54,833 --> 00:19:56,967
Really, Mommy Emma?

289
00:19:57,033 --> 00:19:57,733
Yes.

290
00:19:57,800 --> 00:19:59,000
Let's try.

291
00:19:59,067 --> 00:20:00,300
Come on.

292
00:20:00,367 --> 00:20:01,467
Here you go. There.

293
00:20:01,567 --> 00:20:02,400
Here it is!

294
00:20:02,467 --> 00:20:04,133
Let me see.
I hope there's an ID.

295
00:20:04,200 --> 00:20:05,367
There!

296
00:20:05,433 --> 00:20:07,933
- Here. See?
- There!

297
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:09,133
Can you read it?

298
00:20:09,200 --> 00:20:10,333
Do you know how to read?

299
00:20:13,033 --> 00:20:14,100
What can you say now?

300
00:20:14,167 --> 00:20:14,800
It's here.

301
00:20:14,867 --> 00:20:15,867
There it is!

302
00:20:15,933 --> 00:20:17,233
Ligaya, it's here.

303
00:20:17,300 --> 00:20:18,733
The ambulance is here.

304
00:20:18,800 --> 00:20:20,633
Hurry! Hurry up!

305
00:20:21,933 --> 00:20:23,433
Madam, hang in there.

306
00:20:23,500 --> 00:20:25,233
The ambulance is here, Madam.

307
00:20:31,900 --> 00:20:32,967
Thank goodness.

308
00:20:33,033 --> 00:20:34,900
- Take care of everything.
- Okay, I will.

309
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:37,633
- I know her. I'll go with you.
- Yes, go with them.

310
00:20:37,700 --> 00:20:39,133
There. Everything's good?

311
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:41,133
Ligaya will take care of her.

312
00:20:47,367 --> 00:20:48,067
Go on.

313
00:20:48,133 --> 00:20:49,333
Hold on to me.

314
00:20:50,667 --> 00:20:51,433
Go.

315
00:20:54,333 --> 00:20:55,633
Can you do it?

316
00:20:55,700 --> 00:20:56,967
No?

317
00:20:57,033 --> 00:20:57,900
Wait.

318
00:20:59,833 --> 00:21:01,367
One more?

319
00:21:01,433 --> 00:21:02,133
One more time?

320
00:21:02,200 --> 00:21:03,267
Hold on to me.

321
00:21:10,067 --> 00:21:10,967
Wait.

322
00:21:13,867 --> 00:21:16,033
- Wait.
- Mommy Emma, let's just stop.

323
00:21:17,567 --> 00:21:20,000
Maybe I can never walk again.

324
00:21:21,100 --> 00:21:22,433
Maybe mommy's right.

325
00:21:23,800 --> 00:21:27,100
My legs are hopeless.

326
00:21:31,867 --> 00:21:33,500
It's okay. Never mind.

327
00:21:34,733 --> 00:21:35,767
Mookie?

328
00:21:36,800 --> 00:21:38,733
Can you try once more?

329
00:21:38,800 --> 00:21:40,367
I have an idea.

330
00:21:44,233 --> 00:21:45,433
Right foot first.

331
00:21:47,167 --> 00:21:47,933
Right.

332
00:21:49,567 --> 00:21:50,467
Left.

333
00:21:51,533 --> 00:21:52,500
Right.

334
00:21:53,900 --> 00:21:55,300
Left.

335
00:21:55,367 --> 00:21:56,500
Can you do it?

336
00:21:56,567 --> 00:21:58,633
- I can do it a bit.
- Almost...

337
00:21:58,700 --> 00:21:59,533
Almost there.
Right.

338
00:22:01,500 --> 00:22:03,233
Right.

339
00:22:03,300 --> 00:22:05,033
Hold on to me.

340
00:22:05,100 --> 00:22:06,433
Hold on.

341
00:22:06,500 --> 00:22:07,500
You can do it.

342
00:22:08,533 --> 00:22:09,433
Left.

343
00:22:22,133 --> 00:22:24,767
How are you feeling,
Miss Caparas?

344
00:22:26,400 --> 00:22:29,733
I feel dizzy, but I'm okay.

345
00:22:29,800 --> 00:22:30,667
Can you do it?

346
00:22:30,733 --> 00:22:32,433
Go ahead. Try it.

347
00:22:32,500 --> 00:22:33,433
There.

348
00:22:35,267 --> 00:22:37,100
Mookie!

349
00:22:37,167 --> 00:22:39,300
You can now walk.

350
00:22:39,367 --> 00:22:40,433
- Go on.
- There we go.

351
00:22:42,067 --> 00:22:43,400
I'm supporting you.

352
00:22:43,467 --> 00:22:45,167
I'm just right here.

353
00:22:45,233 --> 00:22:46,633
Okay.

354
00:22:46,700 --> 00:22:48,600
Are you going to let go?

355
00:22:48,700 --> 00:22:49,633
Can you?
- Okay.
- I'll try.

356
00:22:50,667 --> 00:22:51,333
Okay.

357
00:22:56,933 --> 00:22:58,067
It's okay.

358
00:22:58,133 --> 00:22:59,833
It's okay, I can do it.

359
00:22:59,900 --> 00:23:01,300
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

360
00:23:08,667 --> 00:23:10,633
I can do it.

361
00:23:10,700 --> 00:23:12,967
I can do it, Mommy Emma.

362
00:23:13,033 --> 00:23:14,633
You're doing great.

363
00:23:23,333 --> 00:23:24,600
You're doing so much better.

364
00:23:26,733 --> 00:23:28,500
Thank you, Mommy Emma!

365
00:23:28,567 --> 00:23:30,300
You can walk again.

366
00:23:35,700 --> 00:23:38,133
- I didn't know I could do it.
- You're so great.

367
00:23:41,067 --> 00:23:42,133
Mookie?

368
00:23:54,067 --> 00:23:55,567
So it's just a minor injury.

369
00:23:56,633 --> 00:23:59,767
Which means,
I can be discharged.

370
00:24:00,800 --> 00:24:03,367
Miss Caparas, stay in your bed.

371
00:24:03,433 --> 00:24:06,567
I've recommended 48 hours
of observation

372
00:24:06,633 --> 00:24:09,100
when we saw the bumps
and contusions on your head.

373
00:24:09,167 --> 00:24:12,100
You might have delayed reactions
from your trauma.

374
00:24:12,167 --> 00:24:14,800
No, I need to go home.

375
00:24:14,867 --> 00:24:17,167
My daughter needs me.
I'm going home.

376
00:24:17,900 --> 00:24:20,000
Miss Caparas,
please stay in your bed.

377
00:24:20,067 --> 00:24:21,800
- Please stay lying down.
- Ouch!

378
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:25,900
There! Oh my gosh!

379
00:24:25,967 --> 00:24:27,600
Miss Caparas, here, here, here.

380
00:24:27,667 --> 00:24:28,667
Nurse!

381
00:24:32,500 --> 00:24:34,300
You should lie down.
Lie down, lie down.

382
00:24:43,333 --> 00:24:47,233
You know, Dan,
I helped her walk earlier.

383
00:24:47,300 --> 00:24:49,833
I was so happy
because she was so happy.

384
00:24:49,900 --> 00:24:51,267
I was like...

385
00:24:51,333 --> 00:24:51,800
like...
What?

386
00:24:52,833 --> 00:24:54,033
Like a mother?

387
00:24:54,100 --> 00:24:57,333
Emma, there's nothing wrong with
that if Mookie is your daughter.

388
00:24:57,400 --> 00:24:59,400
But she's not, right?

389
00:24:59,467 --> 00:25:02,500
Are you here
to extort money from me?

390
00:25:02,600 --> 00:25:04,700
I understand the word money.

391
00:25:04,767 --> 00:25:08,200
But what does extort mean?

392
00:25:08,267 --> 00:25:09,467
The act of asking
for money from someone.

393
00:25:09,533 --> 00:25:10,667
Oh.

394
00:25:10,733 --> 00:25:12,233
What really is your illness?

395
00:25:12,300 --> 00:25:16,400
I have auto-immune disease
and leukemia.

396
00:25:16,467 --> 00:25:17,733
With all your illnesses,

397
00:25:17,800 --> 00:25:20,033
why is your mom not bringing you
to another doctor?

398
00:25:20,100 --> 00:25:21,900
I don't know either.

399
00:25:21,967 --> 00:25:24,667
Don't you ever try
to stand up and walk.

400
00:25:24,733 --> 00:25:26,367
That's bad for you.

401
00:25:26,433 --> 00:25:27,167
Who's that?

402
00:25:27,233 --> 00:25:28,533
Is that Emma by the door?

403
00:25:28,600 --> 00:25:30,600
What is Emma doing in your room?
